The paper deals with error-correcting codes and their applications in network coding and distributed systems, which are topics that fall under information theory (cs.IT) and coding theory (cs.CC). The paper also discusses the design of codes with support constraints, which is a topic in distributed systems (cs.DS) and signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the paper mentions the GM-MDS conjecture, which is a problem in network information theory (cs.NI).
